%I A395658 #19 May 20 2026 19:14:39
%S A395658 1,1,4,45,2271,1361850
%N A395658 Number of strict ternary closure operators on a set of n elements.
%C A395658 A closure operator cl on a set X is strict if the empty set is closed; it is n-ary if for all subsets S of X, cl(A) being a subset of S for all subsets A of X with cardinality no more than n implies that S is closed.
%C A395658 a(n) is also the number of ternary convexities on a set of n elements (see Kubiś).
%H A395658 Wiesław Kubiś, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/PL00012529">Separation properties of convexity spaces</a>, Journal of Geometry 74 (2002), pp. 110-119.
%H A395658 Tian Vlasic, <a href="/A395658/a395658.py.txt">Python Program</a>
%H A395658 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Closure_operator">Closure operator</a>.
%e A395658 The a(3) = 45 set-systems are the following ({} and {1,2,3} not shown).
